    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offense is positioned for a high-ceiling outing today, headlined by **Gunnar Henderson**, whose 83.29 efficiency score is the clear standard for our lineup. Facing Kai-Wei Teng, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits significantly from an aggressive 16% park adjustment and a favorable platoon matchup, making him our primary engine for power and R/RBI production. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (73.86) also projects as an elite anchor against Payton Tolle; his strong xwOBA profile and a 7% dynamic platoon advantage underscore his reliability in the three-hole. Meanwhile, **Josh Lowe** (69.17) and **Kyle Tucker** (69.35) represent our most efficient outfield assets, both capitalizing on sub-5.00 xERA matchups that provide ample runway for scoring potential.\n\nOur selection process faced a difficult inflection point with the utility spot, where **Nolan Schanuel** (58.79) ultimately edged out **Nasim Nunez** (52.49) for the final active slot. While **Nasim Nunez** is a vital component of our strategy given the league\u2019s premium on stolen bases, his potential impact is neutralized today by a disadvantageous order placement and a negative park adjustment against a stiff Clay Holmes matchup. Conversely, **Nolan Schanuel** provides higher raw volume in a more favorable park context, offering a safer floor for our 5x5 totals. \n\nCaution is warranted with several matchups: **Liam Hicks** faces a daunting test against Shohei Ohtani (2.67 xERA), which suppresses his score to a marginal 40.40, keeping him in the lineup primarily due to positional depth requirements. Additionally, while **Luis Robert Jr.** owns a solid base projection, his score is deflated to 53.66 by a difficult 15% penalty regarding his platoon splits today. All projections remain contingent on the finalization of the \"Lineup Pending\" statuses, as any late-breaking shifts in batting order for **Brady House** or **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** could necessitate a re-evaluation of their respective platoon and order-based bonuses.",
